proposedResponse.body:
Thanks for the question! SkiaSharp (via Skia) does not include a built-in codec for the Netpbm (PPM/PGM/PBM) format — `SKImage.FromEncodedData`, `SKCodec.Create`, and `SKBitmap.Decode` will all return `null` for PPM files. This is consistent across all tested versions (2.88.9, 3.119.0, and main).

However, you can load 24-bit RGB pixel data manually using SkiaSharp's raw pixel APIs. The approach posted by @simonegli8 works well — here's the key pattern:

```csharp
var info = new SKImageInfo(width, height, SKColorType.Rgb888x, SKAlphaType.Opaque);
var bitmap = new SKBitmap(info);
for (int y = 0; y < height; y++)
    for (int x = 0; x < width; x++)
    {
        int i = (y * width + x) * 3;
        bitmap.SetPixel(x, y, new SKColor(rgb[i], rgb[i+1], rgb[i+2]));
    }
```

For better performance on large images, convert the 3-byte-per-pixel RGB data to 4-byte RGBX and use `InstallPixels`, or expand to RGBA and use `SKImage.FromPixelCopy`.

Closing as answered since workarounds are available via the raw pixel APIs.
